  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Measure twice- cut once",
      "body": "Measure and cut all boards to plan lengths."
    },
    {
      "title": "Drill pocket holes",
      "body": "Using your Kreg Pocket Hole Jig- drill the pocket holes for every board in the plan specifications.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/8beaa5b707db9d45.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Router the bed frame boards",
      "body": "Using a router and a 1/2\" straight cut router bit, router the inside edge of each of the bed frame support boards. This should leave a 1/2\" tall by 1/2\" ledge for the bed floor board to rest on.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/2fee97b02c3239d1.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Sand all boards",
      "body": "Using my corded Bosch hand sander to sand each board free of imperfections and splintered wood."
    },
    {
      "title": "Front bed board",
      "body": "Measure and draw the cut line for the front bed board. Use a jig-saw to make this cut. Afterwards sand the angle of the remaining board until you have a smooth flowing opening.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/67f1c55bc509e449.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Bed frame boards",
      "body": "Measure and mark all 4 bed legs on 2 adjacent sides at 4 inches. Assemble the front and rear frame boards. Apply glue to the ends of the frame boards and position and clamp them end to end between 2 leg boards, being careful to line them up to your 4 inch line. Side clamp each joint and screw in your pocket hole screws. Repeat this process with the headboard and foot board. Note* Position the bed frame boards flush with the legs and all other boards to the center of the legs boards",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d240a6876bf58cef.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Side bed boards",
      "body": "Assemble both side frame and rail boards to the already assembled front and rear bed boards. Note* Follow the same board positioning as you did in the previous step.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/b3afed30d562ec7f.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Bottom braces",
      "body": "Install bottom triangle braces to the legs and the bottom of the frame boards.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0bf243c663e8ee6a.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Pocket holes front",
      "body": "Pocket holes placement for the front boards and bottom braces.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/b275adf5ba361afd.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Pocket holes side",
      "body": "Pocket holes placement for the side boards and bottom braces.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/ea4679803dc3845c.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Pocket holes center brace",
      "body": "Pocket holes for the center brace and measurements and placement for the bed floor.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/1b052753b047c3e7.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Bed floor",
      "body": "Cut the bed floor board 32 7/8\" by 21 7/8\" and cut an 1/2\" by 1/2\" notch from each corner. This will allow the floor board to rest completely supported within the bed frame boards.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d8559adc23cf8720.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Side board handles",
      "body": "Using your choice of hardware handles- measure and mount the handles in the center of each of the side boards.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/7b3b21842ada9fe3.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Completed assembly",
      "body": "Apply a stain or clear coat finish to the assembled bed frame and let it dry. Put in a cozy mattress. Add your favorite puppy and then you are done!",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d5503f81583b1866.webp"
    }
  ],
